 He merely motioned `up' with a finger.
 Philetus looked upwards and saw a faint glimmer of light at the end of
 a very long, very lonely tunnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

The light at the end of the tunnel,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 said Philetus with a smirk Sustar could not see.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

That's where we're going.
 Come on, up,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 replied Sustar, the connotations of the phrase lost or ignored.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Philetus shook his head and climbed; he gradually felt lighter the farther
 up they travelled.
 That meant they were going towards the center of the ship, not towards
 the bridge.
 The faint light grew steadily.
 It puzzled him; he felt a sudden pang of instinctive fear in his chest
 and stomach.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\shape italic
There will be no tribunal; they'll slave me.
 Rig me up with the rest of them.
 More dead than alive, yet neither.
 No.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
