\begin_layout Standard
Philetus was suddenly bathed in a warm reddish light that seemed to change
 hue languidly.
 An enormous space unfolded around him, a network of antennae, cables and
 pipes lining its walls.
 A fabulously engineered, metallic skin.
 At both ends, giant blueish cubes could be seen, stacked on top of each
 other, emanating swaths of iridescent light.
 The whole empty chamber seemed to rotate around him at a comfortable speed.
 The light danced around him, hugging him with care; Philetus felt that
 riding the mythical rainbow of Terra could not have been more beautiful
 than this.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\shape italic
The belly of the beast.
 But it's so wonderful, so bright.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

It is, isn't it?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

