\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I'm afraid so.
 The helium-3 mines.
 The energy saving principles in all aspects of your society and life.
 The planned offspring.
 The sanctity of science and technology, the lack of expression like art.
 We have been doing that ever since your forefathers were born.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Our forefathers..
 You've been tailoring us, breeding us since the beginning?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

That is correct.
 Tailored genetic code.
 Qualities that suited us.
 A training and education program that fitted our needs.
 That developed larger cortexes, more memory, more computational power.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I was so terribly right all along.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I tailored you, Philetus.
 I wanted you to be right all along.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Lies.
 Everything has its design limits, you said it yourself; somewhere along
